						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarājakēsarivarman: Year 10 = 994-95 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription refers to the king as ‘who destroyed the ships at Kāndaḷūr-śālai’.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of 12 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for a <hi rend="italic">nandā</hi> lamp to be burnt in the shrine of Gaṇavati (Gaṇapati) in the temple of Tiruneḍuṅgaḷam-uḍaiyār, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadānam</hi> of [Kavira]perumāṉār, by a certain Iḍaikkuḍāṉ Koḷambaṉāch chaṉ of Iḍaikkuḍi in [••••]nāḍu. It is stated that the money was accepted by the temple <hi rend="italic">stāṉapatis</hi> who had agreed to burn the lamp. </p>						

						</summary>
